The first approach is based on [this](https://leetcode.com/problems/valid-permutations-for-di-sequence/discuss/168278/C%2B%2BJavaPython-DP-Solution-O(N2)) post by lee215.

In both the cases we are avoiding looping through the values already looped through by the previous element by just using the previous values to make it O(n^2) instead of O(n^3).
```
// Runtime: 4ms
void firstApproach(string& s, int n, vvi&dp) {
        for (int i =0;i<=n;i++) dp[0][i] = 1;
        for (int i = 1;i<=n;i++) {
            if (s[i-1] == 'I') {
                dp[i][0] = dp[i-1][0];
                for (int j=1;j<=n-i;j++) {
                    dp[i][j] = (dp[i][j-1] + dp[i-1][j])%mod; // summing dp[i-1][0..j]
                }
            } else {
                dp[i][n-i] = dp[i-1][n-i+1];
                for (int j=n-i-1;j>=0;j--) {
                    dp[i][j] = (dp[i][j+1] + dp[i-1][j+1])%mod; // summing dp[i-1][j+1...n-i+1]
                }
            }
        }
    }
```


The second approach is based on the intuitions by wxd_sjtu [here](https://leetcode.com/problems/valid-permutations-for-di-sequence/discuss/196939/Easy-to-understand-solution-with-detailed-explanation), another great explanation by ariawynn [here](https://leetcode.com/problems/valid-permutations-for-di-sequence/discuss/186571/Python-O(N3)O(N2)-time-O(N)-space-DP-solution-with-clear-explanation-(no-%22relative-rank%22-stuff)).
A great visualisation for this approach is also provided by quadpixels [here](https://leetcode.com/problems/valid-permutations-for-di-sequence/discuss/169126/Visualization-Key-to-the-DP-solution:-imagine-cutting-a-piece-of-paper-and-separating-the-halves)

```
// Runtime: 4ms
void secondApproach(string& s, int n, vvi&dp) {
       for (int i=0;i<=n;i++) dp[0][i] = 1;
       for (int i = 1;i<=n;i++) {
           if (s[i-1] == 'I') {
              dp[i][1] = dp[i-1][0];
               for (int j = 2;j<=i;j++) {
                   dp[i][j] = (dp[i][j-1] + dp[i-1][j-1])%mod; // summing dp[i-1][0...j-1]
               } 
           } else {
               dp[i][i-1] = dp[i-1][i-1];
               for (int j = i-2;j>=0;j--) {
                   dp[i][j] = (dp[i][j+1] + dp[i-1][j])%mod; // summing dp[i-1][j...i-1]
               }
           }
       }
   }
