solutions.content:
**Idea:** When the query is for cell `(i, j)`, you actually look for cell `(i + k, j + k)` i.e. the bottom right corner of the required block. The rest of the question is same as [Range Sum Query 2D - Immutable](https://leetcode.com/problems/range-sum-query-2d-immutable). 

Calculate prefix-sum matrix of the matrix. Then subtract out-of-boundary top and right rectangles (prefix sum cells corresponding to them), then add back intersection of these 2 rectangles as you've subtracted the intersection twice. 

Explanation of this logic is in [Approach#4 of Range Sum Query 2D - Immutable](https://leetcode.com/problems/range-sum-query-2d-immutable) and also in this [CV article](https://computersciencesource.wordpress.com/2010/09/03/computer-vision-the-integral-image/).

**T/S:** O(mn), where m x n are the dimensions of the matrix.

```
public int[][] matrixBlockSum(int[][] mat, int k) {
	var prefixSum = getPrefixSum(mat);
	var m = mat.length;
	var n = mat[0].length;
	var blockSum = new int[mat.length][mat[0].length];

	for (var i = 0; i < m; i++) {
		for (var j = 0; j < n; j++) {

			var bottomRightX = Math.min(m, i + 1 + k);
			var bottomRightY = Math.min(n, j + 1 + k);

			var topLeftX = Math.max(0, i - k);
			var topLeftY = Math.max(0, j - k);

			blockSum[i][j] = prefixSum[bottomRightX][bottomRightY] // bottom right corner
					- prefixSum[bottomRightX][topLeftY] // top neighbor of block
					- prefixSum[topLeftX][bottomRightY] // left neighbor of block
					+ prefixSum[topLeftX][topLeftY]; // intersection of top and left neighbors
		}
	}
	return blockSum;
}

private int[][] getPrefixSum(int[][] mat) {
	var prefixSum = new int[mat.length + 1][mat[0].length + 1];
	for (var i = 1; i < prefixSum.length; i++)
		for (var j = 1; j < prefixSum[0].length; j++)
			prefixSum[i][j] = prefixSum[i][j - 1]
					+ prefixSum[i - 1][j]
					- prefixSum[i - 1][j - 1]
					+ mat[i - 1][j - 1];
	return prefixSum;
}
