solutions.content:
Basic idea is to calcualte the cumulative sum of each cell (i,j). Cumulative cell is sum of all cells in rectangular block -> (0, 0) to (i, j)
For a given cell, cumulative cell (i, j) can be formed recursively as
csum(i, j) = val(i, j) + csum(i - 1, j) + csum (i, j - 1) - csum(i - 1, j - 1);
Why we are subtracting csum(i - 1, j - 1), reason is it is being added twice as part of csum(i - 1, j) and csum (i, j - 1)

Say we performed above and created a 2d array of cumulative sums dp[][].

dp[i][j] gives cumulative sum from (0,0) to (i, j)

Once we have cumulative sums, for each cell again we follow the same procedure. For given cell (i, j), all four corners at limit k are
top left (i - k, j - k), top right (i - k, j + k), bottom left (i + k, j - k), bottom right (i + k, j + k)

For cell (i,j) answer is cumulative sum of rectangle (i - k, j - k) to (i + k, j + k). We can calculate the sum of this rectangle using the dp array we created. 

Answer is cumulative sum of the rectangle (0, 0) to bottom right (i + k, j + k) - csum from (0,0) to top right (i - k - 1, j + k) - csum from (0,0) to bottom left (i + k, j - k - 1) + csum from (0,0) to (i - k - 1, j - k - 1).

Again why are we add csum from (0,0) to (i - k - 1, j - k - 1), cause it is removed twice once in csum from (0,0) to top right (i - k - 1, j + k) and then in csum from (0,0) to bottom left (i + k, j - k - 1)

```
public int[][] matrixBlockSum(int[][] mat, int k) {
	int m = mat.length, n = mat[0].length;
	int[][] dp = new int[m][n];
	for(int i = 0; i < m; i++){
		for(int j = 0;j < n; j++){
			if(i > 0){
				dp[i][j] += dp[i - 1][j];
				if(j > 0){
					dp[i][j] -= dp[i - 1][j - 1];
				}
			}
			if(j > 0){
				dp[i][j] += dp[i][j - 1];
			}
			dp[i][j] += mat[i][j];
		}
	}

	for(int i = 0; i < m; i++){
		for(int j = 0; j < n; j++){
			int lri = Math.min(m - 1, i + k), lrj = Math.min(n - 1, j + k);
			int llj = Math.max(0, j - k);
			int uli = Math.max(0, i - k);
			mat[i][j] = dp[lri][lrj];
			if(llj - 1 >= 0){
				mat[i][j] -= dp[lri][llj - 1];
			}
			if(uli - 1 >= 0){
				mat[i][j] -= dp[uli - 1][lrj];
			}
			if(uli - 1 >= 0 && llj - 1 >= 0){
				mat[i][j] += dp[uli - 1][llj - 1];
			}
		}
	}
	return mat;
}
