Time complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)


**IDEA:**

1. Create dummy node and set next to head(given).
2. Take 2 pointers **slow** and **fast** and set to dummy node created in step 1.
3. Advance fast pointer **k** times, now this is our "firstNode", whose value need to be swapped.
4. Now advance **slow** and **fast** pointers till fast is null. At the end slow will point to node which is **n - k** from end. Hence we have our "secondNode".
5. Lastly swap the values of "firstNode" and "secondNode".

**Note**: we are not exactly using slow and fast pointer, just like we do to calculate middle of linked list. Its just that one pointer is k times behind the other pointer.

