# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
This problem can be solved - **Iteratively** OR using **Two Pointers** 
Approach 1 - without additional space, traverse list to the nodes whose val are to be swapped 
Approach 2 - store the val of entire list into a vector, swap the values of the 2 nodes and then update the val of entire list iteratively 

# Approach-1
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We created 2 list pointers,
1. `ListNode *begin` - points at the kth node from the beginning 
2. `ListNode *end` - points at the kth node from the end 

To reach the kth node from the end we first find the length of the string using user defined function `getLength` and then reach the kth node from the end.

We store their "val" in two different integer variables and then swap the values.

Return the head in the end.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:$$O(n)$$ - to find length of the string and traversals 
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:$$O(1)$$ - no additional space or recursion was used 
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
/**
 * Definition for singly-linked list.
 * struct ListNode {
 *     int val;
 *     ListNode *next;
 *     ListNode() : val(0), next(nullptr) {}
 *     ListNode(int x) : val(x), next(nullptr) {}
 *     ListNode(int x, ListNode *next) : val(x), next(next) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    int getLength (ListNode *head)
    {
        int cnt = 0 ; 
        ListNode *temp = head ; 
        while (temp != NULL)
        {
            temp = temp -> next ;
            cnt ++ ; 
        }
        return cnt ;
    }

    ListNode* swapNodes(ListNode* head, int k) {
        ListNode *begin; 
        ListNode *end ; 
        ListNode *temp = head ; 
        if(head == NULL)
        {
            return head ; 
        }
        // list is 1-indexed 
        int cnt1 =1 , cnt2 = 1 ;
        while (cnt1<k && temp != NULL)
        { 
            temp = temp -> next ; 
            cnt1 ++ ; 
        }
        begin = temp ; 
        int first = begin -> val ; 

        // placing temp back on head for 2nd iteration 
        temp = head ; 
        int length = getLength(head) ;
        while (cnt2 < (length-k+1) && temp != NULL)
        {
            temp = temp -> next ; 
            cnt2 ++ ; 
        }
        end = temp ; 
        int second = end -> val;

        // swapping the values of nodes' "val"
        int tmp ; 
        tmp = first ;  
        first = second ; 
        second = tmp ; 

        end->val = second; 
        begin -> val = first ; 

        return head; 
    }
};
```
