solutions.content:
**APPROACH :** 
* We move the left pointer from head till we reaches the Kth node.
* Hance the right node will be K nodes behind the left, so after n = k we move the right pointer till we reache the last node (of current pointer).
* So ultimately left node will be K nodes from left and right one will be K nodes from right of th linked-list.
```
class Solution {
public:
    ListNode* swapNodes(ListNode* head, int k) {
        ListNode *left = head, *right = head, *cur = head;

        int n = 1;
        while(cur!=NULL){
            if (n < k){
                left = left->next;
            }
            if (n > k){
                right = right->next;
            }
            cur = cur->next;
            n++;
        }

        swap(left->val, right->val);

        return head;
    }
};
```
