Here, 
First We Traverse till ```n``` and find nth Node, then we find nth node from the end i.e ```'slow'```
and then we simply swap.
```
class Solution {
    public ListNode swapNodes(ListNode head, int k) {
        if(head == null || head.next == null) return head;

        ListNode dummy = new ListNode(-1);
        dummy.next = head;
        ListNode slow = dummy;
        ListNode fast = dummy;
        ListNode nthNode = dummy;

        for(int i = 0; i<k; i++){                            //Finding nth Node from start
            nthNode = nthNode.next;
            fast = fast.next;
        }

        while(fast!=null){                       //Finding nth Node from end
            fast = fast.next;
            slow = slow.next;
        }

        int temp = nthNode.val;          //Swapping
        nthNode.val = slow.val;
        slow.val = temp;
        return dummy.next;
    }
}
```

